        "content": "<p>General question: should <code>crash</code> call <code>Inspect.toStr</code>. That way you can <code>crash some_context_variable</code> and it will just print the value of <code>some_context_variable</code></p>",
        "id": 491633277,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1735835189
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think it's easy enough to put that inside the string if you want it</p>",
        "id": 491633351,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735835242
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>more explicit that way</p>",
        "id": 491633359,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735835247
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe not that useful and should be left as <code>crash (Inspect.to_str(some_context_variable))</code> or <code>crash \"Some context on the failure: ${Inspect.to_str(some_context_var)}\"</code></p>",
        "id": 491633360,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1735835247
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Sounds good</p>",
